title: Brexit: Supreme Court sets date for judgement
text:
Close share panel Image copyright Supreme Court Image caption The 11 Supreme Court justices (pictured with Lord Toulson - top row, far left - who is now retired) are presiding over the government's appeal The government will learn next Tuesday whether it has won its legal battle to get Brexit under way without the need for a vote by MPs. 
The Supreme Court's judgement follows an appeal against the High Court's rejection of ministers' arguments. 
Theresa May says the government already has powers to invoke Article 50 of the Lisbon Treaty - starting Brexit talks - by the end of March. 
But campaigners say Parliament must be consulted before she does so. 
Labour has already said it will not vote against the government over invoking Article 50, meaning there is very little chance of Mrs May if the matter goes to Parliament.
